>
<h1 id=3D"IntroductionforKafkaComponents-IntendedAudienceforthisGuide:"><sp=
an style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Intended Audience for this Guide:=
</strong></span></h1>
<p>API Developers, who are familiar with Westpac Mesh API development, and =
need to understand:</p>
<ul>
<li>What the key components are for&nbsp;Westpac Mesh Events Kafka</li>
<li>The role of each component, and</li>
<li>How to develop and unit test each component</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"IntroductionforKafkaComponents-UseCase:"><span style=3D"color: rg=
b(0,0,128);"><strong>Use Case:&nbsp;</strong></span></h2>
<p>API developers looking to:&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td rowspan=3D"3" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image confluence-thumbnail" drag=
gable=3D"false" height=3D"181" src=3D"ede50273439cb72e49b9703d6d78d9fa17a8f=
03b117a6f60bbd682d1cef96748" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/120327=
9683/image2020-10-13_11-22-9.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571=
147940&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resour=
ce-id=3D"1203279684" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resourc=
e-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2020-10-13=
_11-22-9.png" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-=
linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-i=
d=3D"1203279683" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"4" alt=3D"" widt=
h=3D"101"></span></p>
</div></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<ul>
<li><strong>Create a working topic in Westpac Mesh:</strong>
<ul>
<li>Initialise your repository for topic development</li>
<li>Complete the Avro model for your topic event record, which can represen=
t one or more&nbsp;Westpac Mesh Kafka events</li>
<li>Build and deploy your topic, which results in a fully-configured topic =
and deployed Avro schema in&nbsp;Westpac Mesh Kafka</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li><strong>Publish Kafka events to a topic:</strong>
<ul>
<li>For a new API, initialise your repository for API development</li>
<li>Extend your API (or Listener) to add a new capability to produce events=
 to&nbsp;Westpac Mesh Kafka</li>
<li>Test your API</li>
</ul></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li><strong>Consume Kafka events from a topic:</strong>
<ul>
<li>Initialise your repository for listener development</li>
<li>Implement the event processing logic for each event type handled from y=
our listener</li>
<li>Implement error handling logic, so that the listener library can retry =
a failed event, or move it to a&nbsp;<em>dead-letter topic</em></li>
</ul></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"IntroductionforKafkaComponents-KeyConcepts:"><span style=3D"color=
: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Key Concepts:</strong></span></h1>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" width=
=3D"468" src=3D"1c1c5680e01d7a34b51f30e934ad7309f97b3d6535c72532b005270b9fe=
6f75b" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279683/image2022-9-23_14=
-2-21.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663905741353&amp;api=3Dv2" da=
ta-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203292089" da=
ta-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" d=
ata-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2022-9-23_14-2-21.png" data-base-=
url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content-=
type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279683" data-li=
nked-resource-container-version=3D"4" alt=3D"" height=3D"261"></span></p>
<p>Usually in Westpac Mesh, we focus solely on an API-centric approach to p=
roviding reusable synchronous services. With Kafka Events, we provide an Ev=
ent-based, publish/subscribe approach to providing reusable&nbsp;<em>Produc=
ers</em>,&nbsp;<em>Listeners</em>, and&nbsp;<em>Topics</em>.</p>
<p>A Producer API component (API with an additional producer capability) pr=
ocesses synchronous REST/HTTPS API requests and produces (or publishes) asy=
nchronously-processed&nbsp;Westpac Mesh Events. The producer interaction wi=
th Kafka is&nbsp;<em>one-way</em>, so a fully modelled event in Westpac Mes=
h Avro format is produced, but only an acknowledgement that the event has b=
een accepted by the&nbsp;<em>topic</em> (not the listener) is returned.</p>
<p>A Listener component listens to (or subscribes to, or consumes) a topic =
for any Westpac Mesh Events, and processes each event using any mixture of =
synchronous API calls or other integrations to SoRs (databases etc), but is=
 not directly coupled to or aware of the specific producer for any event. T=
he listener interaction with Kafka is also&nbsp;<em>one-way</em>, so a full=
y modelled event in Westpac Mesh Avro format is read, but only an acknowled=
gement that the event has been processed (or&nbsp;<em>committed</em>) is se=
nt back to Kafka to track progress against the&nbsp;<em>topic</em> (not the=
 producer).</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper"><i=
mg class=3D"confluence-embedded-image image-center" draggable=3D"false" src=
=3D"83b5c77f234fbd6887c205977b6d8d27dc37a06167bf18e86eec0638f7e57c14" data-=
image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279683/image2020-6-24_19-23-44.png?v=
ersion=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571148273&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresolv=
ed-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279687" data-linked-r=
esource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-=
resource-default-alias=3D"image2020-6-24_19-23-44.png" data-base-url=3D"htt=
ps://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"im=
age/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279683" data-linked-resou=
rce-container-version=3D"4" alt=3D"" width=3D"244" height=3D"539"></span></=
p>
<p>When using&nbsp;Westpac Mesh Events for Kafka, the&nbsp;<em>topic&nbsp;<=
/em>is at the centre of the publish-subscribe topology for a related set of=
 events. So the topic is key for reuse of events allowing more event source=
s (producers) or event sinks (listeners) to be added over time. The Avro sc=
hema for the events must remain compatible for the events to be truly reusa=
ble between producers and listeners. For this reason Westpac Mesh Events fo=
r Kafka always associates each topic with exactly one Avro schema for the e=
vents supported by the records stored in the topic:</p>
<ul>
<li>Changes to a topic schema are always checked using Avro tools to ensure=
 full forward and backward compatibility as minor enhancements are applied;=
</li>
<li>Every event produced is checked for schema compatibility at runtime, to=
 ensure that it will be compatible with any listener subscribed to the topi=
c;</li>
<li>The topic schema is built and published as a maven package, so that pro=
ducers and listeners can include the schema as a Maven dependency (to make =
it easy to include and use the required schema); and</li>
<li>Before merging to master, sign your AVRO schema files as per&nbsp;<a hr=
ef=3D"/display/MESH/How+to+Sign+Component+Contracts+using+Bamboo+Pipeline">=
How to Sign Component Contracts using Bamboo Pipeline</a>. This will be ver=
ified during deployment to <em>sit</em> environment.</li>
</ul>
<p>See&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/MESH/Designing+my+first+Kafka+Topic">Design=
ing my first Kafka Topic</a>&nbsp;for more information, including the schem=
a standards and guidelines.</p>
<p>Each producer has a dependency on the topic, and this dependency require=
s&nbsp;<em>producer</em> access. The developer of the producer can declare =
this dependency in the dependencies.yml file in the project, and the requir=
ed access is configured automatically when the producer is deployed to West=
pac Mesh.</p>
<p>Similarly, each listener&nbsp;has a dependency on the topic, and this de=
pendency requires&nbsp;<em>consumer</em> access. The developer of the liste=
ner can declare this dependency in the dependencies.yml file in the project=
, and the required access is configured automatically when the listener is =
deployed to Westpac Mesh. Because every listener will need a dead-letter to=
pic for failed events, and may need a retry topic, these are also created a=
utomatically for each listener.</p>
<p>Note that for producers and listeners, the&nbsp;<em>topic</em> must also=
 grant access. This is declared in the consumption.yml file in the&nbsp;<em=
>topic</em> project. This ensures that the topic owner is allowing the use =
of the topic (and, importantly the business data in the events).</p>
<p>Note that it is possible to support more than one type of event on a top=
ic, and to add to the set of supported events over time.</p>
<p>For any producer, an additional check is enforced (in the producer libra=
ry) to ensure that every record carries exactly&nbsp;<em>one</em> of the po=
ssible event types.</p>
<p>In any listener, it is important that the listener code implemented by t=
he developer allows for the possibility of new event types that are&nbsp;<e=
m>not</em> handled by the listener. Fortunately this is very easy:</p>
<ul>
<li>the event record for any&nbsp;Westpac Mesh topic will have an optional =
field for each event type (only one of which can be non-null); so</li>
<li>if any event type handled by the listener is non-null, it should be pro=
cessed;</li>
<li>any record containing an event type&nbsp;<em>not</em> handled by the li=
stener can simply be accepted (<em>not</em> treated as an error condition)&=
nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p>Because Kafka is designed to stream records to each listener, skipping r=
ecords is very efficient.</p>
<h2 id=3D"IntroductionforKafkaComponents-BeforeyouStart:"><span style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Before you Start:&nbsp;</strong></span></h2>
<ol>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">TEP has been approved.</span></li=
>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Project Name has been set-up in t=
he&nbsp;Westpac Mesh Service desk<span>.</span></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span>Westpac Mesh&nbsp;Engagemen=
t ticket, for the related project, is in the =E2=80=9C<strong>Build</strong=
>=E2=80=9D stage.</span></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span>Bitbucket Repository has be=
en created as per the process mentioned in the confluence page:&nbsp;<a hre=
f=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/How+to+Create+a+Bit=
bucket+Repository" rel=3D"nofollow">How to Create a Bitbucket Repository</a=
>.</span></span></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Mesh+Deve=
loper+Tools" rel=3D"nofollow">Westpac Mesh Developer Tools</a> are installe=
d on your local machine.</li>
</ol>
<p><br></p>
</div>
<div class=3D"columnMacro" style=3D"width:30%;min-width:30%;max-width:30%;"=
>
<p><br></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279712">Steps to build a Kafka Topic</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"600236fb-9357-4a9e-88ce-82045dfd=
bfac-1203279712">
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-not=
e"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-i=
nformation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Mesh will occasionally need to update the topic build process, for examp=
le:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>When Confluent Kafka platform updates include Avro library changes; or<=
/li>
<li>When the standard event header changes</li>
</ul>
<p>These updates can cause compatibility issues between the Avro libraries =
or generated code. When you rebuild your topic (even with no schema change)=
 the build will use the current Avro version and event header version.</p>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaTopic-StepstobuildaKafkaTopic:"><span style=3D"=
color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Steps to build a Kafka Topic:</strong></span>=
</h1>
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaTopic-Prerequisites:">Prerequisites:</h2>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Kafka topic name&nbsp; is approve=
d &amp; endorsed in confluence page:&nbsp;</span><a href=3D"https://conflue=
nce.srv.westpac.com.au/display/WDPREGO/Topic+Naming+Approvals" rel=3D"nofol=
low">Topic Naming Approvals</a></li>
<li>A&nbsp;Bitbucket repo with the approved Kafka topic name. Refer to&nbsp=
;<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/How+to+Creat=
e+a+Bitbucket+Repository" rel=3D"nofollow">'How to Create a Bitbucket Repos=
itory'</a><span>&nbsp;</span>guide for creating one.</li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"sectionColumnWrapper">
<div class=3D"sectionMacro">
<div class=3D"sectionMacroRow">
<div class=3D"columnMacro" style=3D"width:70%;min-width:70%;max-width:70%;"=
>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 99.=
9466%;">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 3.81963%;">
<col style=3D"width: 96.1273%;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">#</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Actions</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 style=3D"text-align: left;" id=3D"Stepstobui=
ldaKafkaTopic-1"><strong>1</strong></h2></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaTopic-InitialiseComponent"><strong>Initialise C=
omponent</strong></h2>
<p>Initialise Kafka topic component repository using Mesh Dev tools</p>
<ul>
<li>Open Mesh developer tools and run 'init' command</li>
<li>Follow the screen prompts and initialise the API</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>mesh init</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">mesh in=
it -n &lt; approved name of the topic&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>For further help on the commands refer to mesh Developer tools <a href=
=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Mesh+Developer+Tools=
" rel=3D"nofollow">documentation</a>.</p>
</div><p><br></p>
<div id=3D"expander-1726656494" class=3D"expand-container">
<div role=3D"heading" aria-level=3D"6" id=3D"expander-control-1726656494" c=
lass=3D"expand-control"><button type=3D"button" id=3D"expand-button-1726656=
494" class=3D"aui-button aui-button-link aui-button-link-icon-text" aria-ex=
panded=3D"true" aria-controls=3D"expander-content-1726656494"><span class=
=3D"expand-icon aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-chevron-down" aria-hid=
den=3D"true"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text conf-macro-render">S=
ee Example:</span></button>
</div>
<div role=3D"region" id=3D"expander-content-1726656494" class=3D"expand-con=
tent" aria-labelledby=3D"expand-button-1726656494">
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper"><img class=3D"confluenc=
e-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" src=3D"209b7fa3a6481d15639b9986594e51=
944e6073cd3e5e8cc83822a66fb8737639" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments=
/1203279712/image2020-5-12_8-39-51.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1=
663571151023&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-=
resource-id=3D"1203279717" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-r=
esource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2020=
-5-12_8-39-51.png" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" =
data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-contai=
ner-id=3D"1203279712" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"10" alt=3D"=
" width=3D"468" height=3D"241"></span></p>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaTopic-2"><strong>2</=
strong></h2></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaTopic-UpdateSchema">=
<strong>Update&nbsp;Schema</strong></h2><p>The previous step creates the sk=
eleton for a topic with 'Sample.avsc' - sample event schema.</p><p>Replace =
it with the schema for the actual event.&nbsp;</p><p>See instructions.md th=
at was created in the previous step.</p><p><strong>Important</strong>: befo=
re merging to master, sign your AVRO schema files as per&nbsp;<a href=3D"/d=
isplay/MESH/How+to+Sign+Component+Contracts+using+Bamboo+Pipeline">How to S=
ign Component Contracts using Bamboo Pipeline</a>. This will be verified du=
ring deployment to `sit` environment.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaTopic-3"><strong>3</=
strong></h2></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaTopic-AddImportStatements"><strong>Add Import&n=
bsp;Statements</strong></h2>
<p>Browse the component repo for 'event.avdl'&nbsp; This file contains a sc=
hema definition for the topic in Avro IDL format.</p>
<p>This file includes import statements for common schemas for the Event he=
ader and the schema for the header itself.</p>
<p>Add import statements for the event schema and updated the record defini=
tion.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>For more details on IDL format, see&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://avro.a=
pache.org/docs/1.8.1/idl.html" style=3D"text-decoration: underline;" title=
=3D"https://avro.apache.org/docs/1.8.1/idl.html" class=3D"external-link" re=
l=3D"nofollow">https://avro.apache.org/docs/1.8.1/idl.html</a></p>
<p><br></p>
<div id=3D"expander-1715892681" class=3D"expand-container">
<div role=3D"heading" aria-level=3D"6" id=3D"expander-control-1715892681" c=
lass=3D"expand-control"><button type=3D"button" id=3D"expand-button-1715892=
681" class=3D"aui-button aui-button-link aui-button-link-icon-text" aria-ex=
panded=3D"true" aria-controls=3D"expander-content-1715892681"><span class=
=3D"expand-icon aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-chevron-down" aria-hid=
den=3D"true"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text conf-macro-render">S=
ee Example:</span></button>
</div>
<div role=3D"region" id=3D"expander-content-1715892681" class=3D"expand-con=
tent" aria-labelledby=3D"expand-button-1715892681">
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>Sample Avdl</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence"> // Eac=
h event must be defined in AVSC
  import schema "Common.avsc";
  import schema "Created.avsc";
  import schema "DetailChanged.avsc";

  // The Event schema must be versioned in &lt;major&gt;.&lt;minor&gt; form=
at
  @version("1.0")
  record ReferenceEvent {
    // The header declaration is mandatory
    au.com.westpac.wdp.ev.common.EventHeader header;
    // Each event type is an optional field of the event record
    union { null, Created } created =3D null;
    union { null, DetailChanged } detailChanged =3D null;
  }</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaTopic-4"><strong>4</=
strong></h2></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaTopic-MergeChanges">=
<strong>Merge Changes</strong></h2><p>Create a pull request and merge the c=
hanges to the master branch. A successful merge should trigger a build pipe=
line in a dev environment which on completion would generate a jar with Jav=
a classes generated from the Avro. The build pipeline also upserts the sche=
ma registry with the Avro definition in the build.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaTopic-5"><strong>5</=
strong></h2></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaTopic-Maintenance"><strong>Maintenance</strong>=
</h2>
<p>It is necessary to rebuild your topic occasionally, because Confluent Ka=
fka and Avro versions will change over time. This does not change your topi=
c schemas, but it does provide a current build of the topic JAR for any dev=
elopers of Listeners or Producers.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>If an incompatible change is made to your topic schema, deployment will =
fail. This is to protect against data loss (incompatible schemas can't be h=
andled by listeners and those events will be lost).<br><br>
 In dev1, the topic schema can be reset as a self-service activity, this sh=
ould be done for topic in initial development (never deployed to production=
).&nbsp;<span data-teams=3D"true">Try running this plan: <a title=3D"https:=
//bamboo-wdp.srv.westpac.com.au/browse/meshgkops-kakfaresetregdev1" href=3D=
"https://bamboo-wdp.srv.westpac.com.au/browse/MESHGKOPS-KAKFARESETREGDEV1" =
class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://bamboo-wdp.srv.westpac.com=
.au/browse/MESHGKOPS-KAKFARESETREGDEV1</a>.<br><br>
 In higher environments, you must raise a Mesh service request for a topic =
schema reset.<br><br></span></p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-not=
e"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-i=
nformation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Topic schema reset in production will typically cause&nbsp;<strong>data =
loss</strong> in production, so you should ensure in development and testin=
g that only&nbsp;<em>compatible</em> schema changes are made.<br><br>
 Otherwise, you would create a new 'v2' topic, and migrate all producers an=
d listeners to use it (side-by-side migration) as we do for major API chang=
es.</p>
</div>
</div>
<p><span data-teams=3D"true">&nbsp;</span></p>
</div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"columnMacro" style=3D"width:30%;min-width:30%;max-width:30%;"=
>
<p><br></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279740">Steps to build a Kafka Producer</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"600236fb-9357-4a9e-88ce-82045dfd=
bfac-1203279740">
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaProducer-StepstobuildaKafkaProducer:"><span sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Steps to build a Kafka Producer:</stron=
g></span></h1>
<p>Any API may be a Kafka Producer. The ability to produce events to Mesh K=
afka is a capability of an API. In addition, other component types (initial=
ly, Kafka Listeners) may also be a Kafka Producer.</p>
<p>You may be creating a new API, or adding a new capability to an existing=
 API.</p>
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaProducer-Prerequisites:">Prerequisites:</h2>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Kafka Producer API name&nbsp; is =
approved &amp; endorsed in confluence page:&nbsp;</span><a style=3D"text-de=
coration: none;text-align: left;" href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.co=
m.au/display/WDPREGO/API+Naming+Approvals" rel=3D"nofollow">API Naming Appr=
ovals</a></li>
<li>A&nbsp;Bitbucket repo with the approved Kafka Producer API name. Refer =
to&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/How+t=
o+Create+a+Bitbucket+Repository" rel=3D"nofollow">'How to Create a Bitbucke=
t Repository'</a> guide for creating one.</li>
<li>Your API must be a Java API using the Tomcat 9 container.</li>
<li>A Topic to produce messages to- see&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.=
srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Steps+to+build+a+Kafka+Topic?src=3Dcontextn=
avpagetreemode" rel=3D"nofollow">Steps to build a Kafka Topic</a>.</li>
<li>If you want to produce events to an existing topic, an approval from th=
e topic owner to produce to the topic. is needed.</li>
<li>Request access to dev Kafka (for unit testing from your laptop): <a hre=
f=3D"/display/MESH/How+to+Request+ZScaler+Private+Access+for+Mesh+Kafka+Dev=
elopment">How to Request ZScaler Private Access for Mesh Kafka Development<=
/a></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-not=
e"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-i=
nformation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>If your producer needs to produce events to more than one topic, you nee=
d to ensure that the build artefacts you include (your POM dependency on ea=
ch topic JAR) are compatible. The easiest way of doing this is to simply us=
e a current build of each topic.</p>
<p>There is a specific issue affecting a producer that includes topic JARs =
built with different versions of Avro (built for different version of the p=
latform as it is upgraded over time).</p>
<p>This causes clashing definitions of the common event header included in =
every event on every topic.</p>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"sectionColumnWrapper">
<div class=3D"sectionMacro">
<div class=3D"sectionMacroRow">
<div class=3D"columnMacro" style=3D"width:70%;min-width:70%;max-width:70%;"=
>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 99.=
9617%;">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 1.65588%;">
<col style=3D"width: 98.3536%;">
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p>#</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p>Actions</p></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"Stepstobui=
ldaKafkaProducer-1"><strong>1</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaProducer-InitialiseComponentRepository"><strong=
>Initialise Component Repository&nbsp;</strong></h2>
<p>This step is required only for a new API.</p>
<p>Initialize Kafka Producer API component repository using <a href=3D"http=
s://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Mesh+Developer+Tools" rel=3D=
"nofollow">Mesh Developer Tools</a>:</p>
<ul>
<li>Open Mesh developer tools and run 'incubate' command</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>mesh incubate</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">mesh in=
cubate -n &lt; approved repo name of the producer&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p>For further help on the commands refer to Mesh Developer tools <a href=
=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Mesh+Developer+Tools=
" rel=3D"nofollow">documentation</a>.</p>
<p><br></p>
<div id=3D"expander-1767369718" class=3D"expand-container">
<div role=3D"heading" aria-level=3D"6" id=3D"expander-control-1767369718" c=
lass=3D"expand-control"><button type=3D"button" id=3D"expand-button-1767369=
718" class=3D"aui-button aui-button-link aui-button-link-icon-text" aria-ex=
panded=3D"true" aria-controls=3D"expander-content-1767369718"><span class=
=3D"expand-icon aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-chevron-down" aria-hid=
den=3D"true"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text conf-macro-render">S=
ee Example:</span></button>
</div>
<div role=3D"region" id=3D"expander-content-1767369718" class=3D"expand-con=
tent" aria-labelledby=3D"expand-button-1767369718">
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper"><img class=3D"confluenc=
e-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" src=3D"a4bd812718958fc890993e2c37623d=
