sion=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571155187&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresolved=
-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279765" data-linked-res=
ource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-re=
source-default-alias=3D"image2020-4-24_9-8-24.png" data-base-url=3D"https:/=
/confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/=
png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279740" data-linked-resource-=
container-version=3D"16" alt=3D"" width=3D"468" height=3D"166"></span></p>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"Stepstobui=
ldaKafkaProducer-3"><strong>3</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaProducer-GenerateCode"><strong>Generate Code&nb=
sp;</strong></h2>
<p>Generate code from the swagger:</p>
<ul>
<li>Place your latest approved swagger in your API repository directory.</l=
i>
<li>Run 'gencode' command with 'jaxrs' as implementation.</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>Generate code from the swagger</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">mesh ge=
ncode -i  jaxrs</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>Westpac Mesh uses Spring-Kafka as the base f=
ramework for the Kafka consumer/producer implementation., which has a depen=
dency on spring core libraries. You can have&nbsp;<span>your -</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span> API implemented using 'jax-rs' and use spring only for dependenc=
y injection.<a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/re=
pos/wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-integ-ref-springkafkaproducer-v1-api/browse" cl=
ass=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow"> Reference kafka producer implementa=
tion</a> follows this approach.</span></li>
<li>API implemented using 'Spring MVC'.</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<div id=3D"expander-1800585235" class=3D"expand-container">
<div role=3D"heading" aria-level=3D"6" id=3D"expander-control-1800585235" c=
lass=3D"expand-control"><button type=3D"button" id=3D"expand-button-1800585=
235" class=3D"aui-button aui-button-link aui-button-link-icon-text" aria-ex=
panded=3D"true" aria-controls=3D"expander-content-1800585235"><span class=
=3D"expand-icon aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-chevron-down" aria-hid=
den=3D"true"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text conf-macro-render">S=
ee Example:</span></button>
</div>
<div role=3D"region" id=3D"expander-content-1800585235" class=3D"expand-con=
tent" aria-labelledby=3D"expand-button-1800585235">
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper"><img class=3D"confluenc=
e-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" src=3D"14eb9df91a53243c4e3752b6e524bd=
8045414c9395efd182b8625967fee9f626" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments=
/1203279740/image2020-4-28_5-13-9.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D16=
63571154760&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-r=
esource-id=3D"1203279759" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-re=
source-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2020-=
4-28_5-13-9.png" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" da=
ta-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-containe=
r-id=3D"1203279740" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"16" alt=3D"" =
width=3D"468" height=3D"191"></span></p>
</div>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=
=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaProducer-4"><strong>4</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaProducer-IncludeDependencies"><strong>Include D=
ependencies</strong></h2>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Follow the instructions provided i=
n '<a href=3D"http://instructions.md" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofoll=
ow">instructions.md</a>' to</span></p>
<ul style=3D"text-align: left;">
<li>Include&nbsp;lib-westpac-digital-platform-springkafkaproducer&nbsp;jar =
in your API POM.</li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Include the jar with Avro beans t=
hat correspond to the Avro schema of the target topic.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Add spring boot dependencies in yo=
ur POM.</span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><strong>Note:</strong> '&nbsp;lib-=
westpac-digital-platform-springkafkaproducer' has spring-boot auto-configur=
ation feature enabled. If<span>&nbsp;</span><code style=3D"text-align: left=
;">spring-boot-autoconfigure</code><span>&nbsp;</span>library is present in=
 the application classpath, spring boot scans this library for component de=
finitions, and instantiates all required beans.</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">If you are not using spring boot, =
you have to include '<code><a href=3D"http://au.com" class=3D"external-link=
" rel=3D"nofollow">au.com</a>.westpac.spring.kafka.producer.autoconfigure</=
code>' package in your component scan.</span></p>
<p><br></p>
