</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279769">Steps to build a Kafka Listener</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"600236fb-9357-4a9e-88ce-82045dfd=
bfac-1203279769">
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListener-StepstobuildaKafkaListener:"><span sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Steps to build a Kafka Listener:</stron=
g></span></h1>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"sectionColumnWrapper">
<div class=3D"sectionMacro">
<div class=3D"sectionMacroRow">
<div class=3D"columnMacro" style=3D"width:70%;min-width:70%;max-width:70%;"=
>
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListener-Prerequisites:">Prerequisites:</h2>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Kafka Listener name&nbsp; is appr=
oved &amp; endorsed in confluence page:&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/WDPREGO/To=
pic+Listener+Naming+Approvals">Topic Listener Naming Approvals</a></span></=
li>
<li>A&nbsp;Bitbucket repo with the approved Kafka Listener API name. Refer =
to&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/How+t=
o+Create+a+Bitbucket+Repository" rel=3D"nofollow">'How to Create a Bitbucke=
t Repository'</a> guide for creating one.</li>
<li>A Topic to consume messages from.</li>
<li>If you want to consume events from an existing topic, an approval from =
the topic owner is needed.</li>
<li>Request access to dev Kafka (for unit testing from your laptop): <a hre=
f=3D"/display/MESH/How+to+Request+ZScaler+Private+Access+for+Mesh+Kafka+Dev=
elopment">How to Request ZScaler Private Access for Mesh Kafka Development<=
/a></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-not=
e"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-i=
nformation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>If your listener also needs to produce events to one or more topics, you=
 need to ensure that the build artefacts you include (your POM dependency o=
n each topic JAR) are compatible. The easiest way of doing this is to simpl=
y use a current build of each topic.</p>
<p>There is a specific issue affecting a listener that includes topic JARs =
built with different versions of Avro (built for different version of the p=
latform as it is upgraded over time).</p>
<p>This causes clashing definitions of the common event header included in =
every event on every topic.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 95.=
797%;">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 2.0985%;">
<col style=3D"width: 38.4154%;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">#</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Actions&nbsp;</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListener-1"><strong>=
1</strong></h2></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListener-InitialiseListenerComponent"><strong>I=
nitialise Listener Component</strong></h2>
<p>Initialise Kafka Listener component repository using Mesh Dev tools</p>
<ul>
<li>Open Mesh developer tools and run 'incubate' command</li>
<li>Follow the screen prompts and initialise the API</li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>mesh incubate</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">mesh in=
cubate -n &lt; approved repo name of the listener&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>For further help on the commands refer to Mesh Developer tools <a href=
=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Mesh+Developer+Tools=
" rel=3D"nofollow">documentation</a>.</p>
<p><br></p>
<div id=3D"expander-697882334" class=3D"expand-container">
<div role=3D"heading" aria-level=3D"6" id=3D"expander-control-697882334" cl=
ass=3D"expand-control"><button type=3D"button" id=3D"expand-button-69788233=
4" class=3D"aui-button aui-button-link aui-button-link-icon-text" aria-expa=
nded=3D"true" aria-controls=3D"expander-content-697882334"><span class=3D"e=
xpand-icon aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-chevron-down" aria-hidden=
=3D"true"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text conf-macro-render">See =
Example:</span></button>
</div>
<div role=3D"region" id=3D"expander-content-697882334" class=3D"expand-cont=
ent" aria-labelledby=3D"expand-button-697882334">
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper"><img class=3D"confluenc=
e-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" src=3D"75d2e4ffab440df01868f9f63655c5=
7f72dd611b3598fe96492e367f401c7ddb" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments=
/1203279769/image2020-5-12_8-38-4.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D16=
63571158887&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-r=
esource-id=3D"1203279790" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-re=
source-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2020-=
5-12_8-38-4.png" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" da=
