r-id=3D"1203279769" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"17" alt=3D"" =
width=3D"468" height=3D"290"></span></p>
</div>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListener-2"><strong>=
2</strong></h2></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListener-Refactor"><=
strong>Refactor</strong></h2><p>The previous step&nbsp;creates a skeleton i=
mplementation (EventListener.java) of '<span>WdpKafkaListener'.</span></p><=
p><span>Refactor EventListener.java to rename and implement your business l=
ogic in the '</span>handleMessage' method.</p><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(=
23,43,77);">This <span> '</span>handleMessage' method gets invoked when the=
 Kafka container receives an event.</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListener-3"><strong>=
3</strong></h2></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListener-ImplementErrorHandling"><strong>Implem=
ent Error Handling</strong></h2>
<p>Implement error handling&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>If the event processing encounters an exception that is retry-able (lik=
e technical exceptions), you can retry the event by wrapping the exception =
in an instance of WdpKafkaRetryableException and throwing back to the conta=
iner.</li>
<li>If the event processing encounters an exception that is not retry-able =
(like business exceptions), you should wrap the exception in an instance of=
 WdpKafkaNonRetryableException and throwback to the container.</li>
<li>By default, any unhandled exceptions that are encountered while process=
ing the event are treated as non-retry-able.</li>
<li>Optionally,&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://bitbucket.s=
rv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDPCOM/repos/lib-westpac-digital-platform-retryc=
ontext-schema/browse/src/main/schema/RetryContext.schema.json" style=3D"tex=
t-decoration: none;" rel=3D"nofollow">RetryContext<span>&nbsp;</span></a>-t=
he placeholder for the exception details returned from API invocation, retr=
y metadata as a key-value pair, can be provided while instantiating&nbsp;Wd=
pKafkaRetryableException/WdpKafkaNonRetryableException.</li>
<li>Retry context provided in the previous step is populated in the KafkaRe=
cordHeaders while publishing the event to DLT. This context information can=
 be used while processing failed events from the DLT.</li>
</ul>
<p>Full implementation of error handling can be found in the <a href=3D"htt=
ps://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/wdp-cap-technolmgt-plt=
f-integ-ref-spring-kafka-v1-listener/browse" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D=
"nofollow">reference listener</a>.</p>
<p><br></p>
<div id=3D"expander-1446241199" class=3D"expand-container">
<div role=3D"heading" aria-level=3D"6" id=3D"expander-control-1446241199" c=
lass=3D"expand-control"><button type=3D"button" id=3D"expand-button-1446241=
199" class=3D"aui-button aui-button-link aui-button-link-icon-text" aria-ex=
panded=3D"true" aria-controls=3D"expander-content-1446241199"><span class=
=3D"expand-icon aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-chevron-down" aria-hid=
den=3D"true"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text conf-macro-render">S=
ee Example:</span></button>
</div>
<div role=3D"region" id=3D"expander-content-1446241199" class=3D"expand-con=
tent" aria-labelledby=3D"expand-button-1446241199">
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>Sample Error Handling</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence"> public=
 void handleMessage(ConsumerRecord&lt;String, ReferenceEvent&gt; consumerRe=
cord) {

        try {
            //Your business logic should go here
     =20
        } catch (HttpClientErrorException | HttpServerErrorException restCl=
ientEx) {
             if (restClientEx.getStatusCode() =3D=3D HttpStatus.TOO_MANY_RE=
QUESTS ||
                restClientEx.getStatusCode().series() =3D=3D HttpStatus.Ser=
ies.SERVER_ERROR) {
            throw new WdpKafkaRetryableException(key, "Failed to process me=
ssage", buildRetryContext(restClientEx), restClientEx);
             } else {
             throw new WdpKafkaNonRetryableException(key, "Failed to proces=
s message", buildRetryContext(restClientEx), restClientEx);

           }
        } catch (Exception e) {
            LOGGER.log(Level.SEVERE,"Encountered exception :", e);
            throw e;
        }

    }

   private RetryContext buildRetryContext(HttpStatusCodeException restClien=
tEx) {
        RetryContext context =3D new RetryContext();
        List&lt;RetryContextDetail&gt; retryContextDetailList =3D new Array=
List&lt;&gt;();
        RetryContextDetail detail =3D new RetryContextDetail();
        detail.setKey("Failed API");
        detail.setValue("Insert API name");
        retryContextDetailList.add(detail);
        context.setRetryContextDetails(retryContextDetailList);
        return context;
    }

</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListen=
er-4"><strong>4</strong></h2></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListener-ConfigureRetryProperties"><strong>Conf=
igure Retry Properties</strong></h2>
<p>Configure Retry properties</p>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">WdpKafkaListener c</span><span st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">an retry an event on an exception from the li=
stener implementation using a simple retry and exponential back-off policy.=
 </span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Wrap any exception you want to re=
try as</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">&nbsp;WdpKafkaRetryableE=
xception</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">and any exception you =
don't want to retry as</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">&nbsp;Wd=
pKafkaNonRetryableException</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">. <=
/span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">On exhausting all retries, the ev=
ent is published to dead letter topic with any retry context passed in the =
exception. </span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">By default, retry functionality i=
s configured with the following values. One can override default values by =
defining custom values in</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">&nbsp=
;'<strong>kafka-consumer.properties'</strong> file&nbsp;</span><span style=
=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">with an appropriate key.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<div id=3D"expander-374395739" class=3D"expand-container">
<div role=3D"heading" aria-level=3D"6" id=3D"expander-control-374395739" cl=
ass=3D"expand-control"><button type=3D"button" id=3D"expand-button-37439573=
9" class=3D"aui-button aui-button-link aui-button-link-icon-text" aria-expa=
nded=3D"true" aria-controls=3D"expander-content-374395739"><span class=3D"e=
xpand-icon aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-chevron-down" aria-hidden=
=3D"true"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text conf-macro-render">See =
Example:</span></button>
</div>
<div role=3D"region" id=3D"expander-content-374395739" class=3D"expand-cont=
ent" aria-labelledby=3D"expand-button-374395739">
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" data-mce-resize=3D"=
false">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 2.0985%;">
<col style=3D"width: 38.4154%;">
<col style=3D"width: 59.4433%;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable" data-mce-resize=3D"false">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Property K=
ey</span></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Description</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">default value</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>retry.initial.interval</code></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">The 'initialInterval' value in milli-sec</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">100</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>retry.multiplier</code></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">The 'multiplier' value</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">2</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>retry.max.interval</code></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">maximum backoff time in milli-sec</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">30000</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>max.retry.attempts</code></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">The limit to the number of attempts&nbsp;</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">3</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div><p>The defaults above result in the following retry behavior (assumin=
g retryable exceptions):</p>
<ul>
<li>after the first attempt fails, backoff will wait 100ms before retry</li=
>
<li>after the second attempt fails, backoff will wait 200ms before retry</l=
i>
<li>after the third attempt fails, the event goes to DLT</li>
</ul><p><br></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListen=
er-5"><strong>5</strong></h2></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListen=
er-Optional:"><strong>Optional:</strong></h2><p>While most of the propertie=
s&nbsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">required for connecting to Kaf=
ka brokers are auto-configured by Mesh Kafka listener library, users can us=
e&nbsp;<strong>kafka-consumer.properties </strong>to supplement the consume=
r config.</span></p><p><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Note</=
span></strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">: '</span><span style=
=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">kafka-consumer.properties 'should not be used to=
 inject any properties other than Kafka consumer configuration or override =
Mesh injected properties. For a full list of Mesh injected properties refer=
 <a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDPCOM/repos/lib-=
westpac-digital-platform-springkafkalistener/browse/README.md" class=3D"ext=
ernal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">read.me</a>.</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListen=
er-6"><strong>6</strong></h2></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListen=
er-Optional:.1"><strong>Optional:</strong></h2><p><span style=3D"color: rgb=
(23,43,77);">Every consumer is bundled with a Kafka producer to publish fai=
led events to the Dead letter topic. All the properties for the DLT publish=
er are injected by the listener library, users can use&nbsp;<strong>kafka-p=
roducer.properties </strong>to supplement the DLT publisher config.</span><=
/p><p><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Note</span></strong><sp=
an style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">: '</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,4=
3,77);">kafka-producer.properties 'should not be used to inject any propert=
ies other than Kafka producer configuration for DLT publishing or override =
Mesh injected properties. For a full list of Mesh injected properties refer=
 <a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDPCOM/repos/lib-=
westpac-digital-platform-springkafkalistener/browse/README.md" class=3D"ext=
ernal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">read.me</a>.</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListen=
er-7"><strong>7</strong></h2></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListen=
er-PublishandTest"><strong>Publish and Test</strong></h2><p>Publishing a me=
ssage&nbsp; using 'testproducer' utility for testing</p>
<ul>
<li>During development, it might be useful to publish a message to the topi=
c in a dev environment, which could be consumed by the listener locally / l=
istener in dev environment for testing the functionality.</li>
<li>Mesh provides a 'testproducer' utility to support publishing an event.<=
/li>
<li>This test producer is a standalone component, developed solely to publi=
sh events, that can be run independently of the listener.</li>
<li>Refer to&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/=
WDPCOM/repos/lib-westpac-digital-platform-kafka-testproducer/browse/readme.=
md" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">kafka-testproducer</a> for run=
ning the utility</li>
</ul><p><br></p><p><br></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListen=
er-8"><strong>8</strong></h2></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListener-FunctionalTestingtheListener"><strong>=
Functional Testing the Listener</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>Westpac Mesh uses canary deployment (a deployment in which the new vers=
ion of the deployable is tested before beginning a rolling update) to ensur=
e safe application rollout to an environment. As a listener can only be inv=
oked by publishing an event to a topic and the old version of the listener =
was already subscribed to the topic, it is difficult to test the functional=
ity of a new version of a Kafka listener to be promoted without causing an =
outage.</li>
<li><span>To get around this problem Mesh Kafka listener library provides a=
n HTTP endpoint that invokes the handleMessage method in the Kafka listener=
 implementation. </span></li>
<li><span>Similar to the newman test suite used for testing the API functio=
nality, developers can include&nbsp;</span><span>their functional tests in =
the newman suite that gets executed during the canary deployment.</span></l=
i>
<li><span>These tests call handleMessage synchronously, and so success or a=
ny errors (Exceptions) will be reported in the HTTP response.</span></li>
<li><span>If any of the assertion in the&nbsp; test suite fails, the deploy=
ment will be failed and the updated version will not be rolled in.</span></=
li>
</ul>
<p><span>To enable functional testing in your listener project</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Bootstrap&nbsp;the functional tes=
ting resource using JAX-RS resource binding.</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Bundle functional test suite in t=
he api-tests folder</span></li>
</ul>
<p><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Note:&nbsp;<span style=3D"=
color: rgb(51,51,51);">The functional tests invoke live endpoints of downst=
ream systems in a given environment. This could result in data integrity is=
sues if your test causes your listener to invoke any non-idempotent back en=
d systems.</span></span></strong></p>
<p><br></p>
<div id=3D"expander-799637854" class=3D"expand-container">
<div role=3D"heading" aria-level=3D"6" id=3D"expander-control-799637854" cl=
