er-11"><strong>11</strong></h2></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListen=
er-KafkaListenerandSwimlaneSupport"><strong>Kafka Listener and Swimlane Sup=
port</strong></h2><p>Just like a Mesh API, Kafka listener API&nbsp; support=
s virtual swimlanes. The process to enroll, deploy, and undeploy a swimlane=
 is the same as that of a normal API. Refer to Mesh Developer tools <a href=
=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/WDPIPAAS/Mesh+Developer+T=
ools" rel=3D"nofollow">documentation</a>&nbsp;for swimlane operations.&nbsp=
;&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListen=
er-12"><strong>12</strong></h2></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaListener-TestingListenerCodeLocally:"><strong>T=
esting Listener Code Locally:</strong></h2>
<p>A listener can be run from on your local workstation with a little bit o=
f configuration.</p>
</div><p><strong>For Confluent cloud</strong>:</p><p>The process for testin=
g your listener that connects to a topic migrated to Confluent cloud is by =
using generic DEV credentials (early adopter functional account) which has =
access to all topics in the DEV cluster. Early adopter credentials for conn=
ecting to DEV Kafka cluster is provided in this page: <a href=3D"/display/M=
D/Early+Adopter+Credentials+for+Confluent+Cloud+DEV+cluster">Early Adopter =
Credentials for Confluent Cloud DEV cluster</a></p><p>Follow the below step=
s to configure:</p>
<ul>
<li>Create a file named 'wdp-kafka.properties' in the env/local folder.</li=
>
<li>Update the file as shown in below sample titled wdp-kafka.properties.</=
li>
<li>Add the topic and group ID details to the file. This can be retrieved f=
rom the Configure access stage logs of the pipeline in listener deployment.=
</li>
<li>Create a file named 'wdp-kafka-secrets.properties' in secrets/local fol=
der.</li>
<li>Update the file as shown in below sample titled wdp-kafka-secrets.prope=
rties</li>
<li>At this moment, a listener cannot be run from mesh developer tools. But=
 the pom entries generated by the 'mesh init' include a cargo container plu=
gin which can be used to run the listener code.</li>
</ul><p><br></p>
<div id=3D"expander-965534174" class=3D"expand-container">
<div role=3D"heading" aria-level=3D"6" id=3D"expander-control-965534174" cl=
