<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279797">Kafka Event Helper Library</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"600236fb-9357-4a9e-88ce-82045dfd=
bfac-1203279797">
<p>This library has a set of useful classes to help with Mesh Kafka Events.=
</p>
<h1 id=3D"KafkaEventHelperLibrary-EventHeaderHelper"><u>EventHeaderHelper</=
u></h1>
<p><em>EventHeaderHelper</em> is a helper wrapper on EventHeader. It will p=
rovide an EventHeader.Builder with pre-filled fields with a mandatory gener=
ated value. Clients can then use this Builder to populate additional fields=
 and build, to obtain an EventHeader.</p>
<p>The library has following versions:</p>
<p><strong>1.0.1</strong> - for events adhering to wdp-ev-common-v1-schema =
version series 1.0</p>
<p><strong>2.0.0</strong> - for events adhering to wdp-ev-common-v1-schema =
version series 2.0</p>
<h1 id=3D"KafkaEventHelperLibrary-EventUtils"><u>EventUtils</u></h1>
<p>This class contains a set of utility methods to help with conversion of =
Date, Time and Timestamp from Swagger format to Avro format and vice-versa.=
</p>
<p>The following utility methods are available:</p>
<p><em>avroDateToSwaggerDate</em> - converts AVRO Logical Type Date to RFC3=
339 format Date. <em>[ eg: 18262&nbsp;=E2=86=92 2020-01-01 ]</em></p>
<p><em>swaggerDateToAvroDate</em> - converts RFC3339 format Date to AVRO Lo=
gical Type Date.&nbsp;<em>[ eg: 2021-01-01 =E2=86=92 18628 ]</em></p>
<p><em>avroTimeToSwaggerTime</em> - converts AVRO Logical Type Time-Millis =
to RFC3339 format Time.&nbsp;<em>[ eg: 73220202 =E2=86=92 20:20:20.202 ]</e=
m></p>
<p><em>swaggerTimeToAvroTime</em> - converts RFC3339 format Time to AVRO Lo=
gical Type Time-Millis.&nbsp;<em>[ eg: 12:00:00 =E2=86=92 43200000 ]</em></=
p>
<p><em>avroTimestampToSwaggerDateTime</em> - converts AVRO Logical Type Tim=
estamp-Millis to RFC3339 format DateTime.&nbsp;<em>[ eg: 0&nbsp;=E2=86=92&n=
bsp;1970-01-01T00:00:00Z ]</em></p>
<p><em>swaggerDateTimeToAvroTimestamp</em> - converts RFC3339 format DateTi=
me to AVRO Logical Type Timestamp-Millis.&nbsp;<em>[ eg:&nbsp;2020-01-01T20=
:02:20.020Z =E2=86=92&nbsp;1577908940020 ]</em></p>
<h2 id=3D"KafkaEventHelperLibrary-Howtouse">How to use</h2>
<p>You can add the following compile-time dependency in your pom.xml:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: xml; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">&lt;depe=
ndency&gt;
=09&lt;groupId&gt;au.com.westpac.wdp.commons.westpac.digital.platform&lt;/g=
roupId&gt;
=09&lt;artifactId&gt;kafka-event-helper&lt;/artifactId&gt;
=09&lt;version&gt;2.0.0&lt;/version&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"KafkaEventHelperLibrary-UsingEventHeaderHelper">Using EventHeader=
Helper</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">// get =
an EventHeader.Builder using the helper, which has pre-populated eventId, o=
ccurredOn, detectedOn, expiresOn fields.
EventHeader eventHeader =3D EventHeaderHelper.newBuilder()
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09// set other fields as per client requirements
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09.setAppCorrelationId(xAppCorrelationId)
                    =09=09.setBrandSilo(EnumBrandSilo.Other)
                    =09=09.setOrganisationId(EnumOrganisationId.valueOf(xOr=
ganisationId))
                    =09=09.setOriginatingSystemId(xOriginatingSystemId)
                    =09=09.setProducerId(API_NAME)
                    =09=09.setConsumerType(EnumConsumerType.valueOf(xConsum=
erType))
                    =09=09.setUserId(xUserId)
                    =09=09.setUserIdScheme(xUserIdScheme !=3D null ? EnumUs=
erIdScheme.valueOf(xUserIdScheme) : null)
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09// and build as usual to get an instance of EventHeade=
r
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09.build();</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"KafkaEventHelperLibrary-UsingEventUtils">Using EventUtils</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">// conv=
erts RFC3339 format Date to AVRO Logical Type Date.&nbsp;[ eg: 2021-01-01 =
=E2=86=92 18628 ]
Integer avroDate =3D EventUtils.swaggerDateToAvroDate(LocalDate.now().toStr=
ing())

// converts RFC3339 format Time to AVRO Logical Type Time-Millis.&nbsp;[ eg=
: 12:00:00 =E2=86=92 43200000 ]
Integer avroTimeMillis =3D EventUtils.swaggerTimeToAvroTime(LocalTime.now()=
.toString())

// converts RFC3339 format DateTime to AVRO Logical Type Timestamp-Millis.&=
nbsp;[ eg:&nbsp;2020-01-01T20:02:20.020Z =E2=86=92&nbsp;1577908940020 ]
Long avroTimestampMillis =3D EventUtils.swaggerDateTimeToAvroTimestamp(Inst=
ant.now().toString())

// converts AVRO Logical Type Date to RFC3339 format Date. [ eg: 18262&nbsp=
;=E2=86=92 2020-01-01 ]
String swaggerDate =3D EventUtils.avroDateToSwaggerDate(avroDate)

// converts AVRO Logical Type Time-Millis to RFC3339 format Time.&nbsp;[ eg=
: 73220202 =E2=86=92 20:20:20.202 ]
String swaggerTime =3D EventUtils.avroTimeToSwaggerTime(avroTimeMillis)

// converts AVRO Logical Type Timestamp-Millis to RFC3339 format DateTime.&=
nbsp;[ eg: 0&nbsp;=E2=86=92&nbsp;1970-01-01T00:00:00Z ]
String swaggerDateTime =3D EventUtils.avroTimestampToSwaggerDateTime(avroTi=
mestampMillis)</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"KafkaEventHelperLibrary-References">References</h2>
<p><a href=3D"https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3339" class=3D"external-link" =
rel=3D"nofollow">https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3339</a><br><a href=3D"http=
s://avro.apache.org/docs/1.9.2/spec.html#Logical+Types" class=3D"external-l=
ink" rel=3D"nofollow">https://avro.apache.org/docs/1.9.2/spec.html#Logical+=
Types</a></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1409164991">Steps to build a .Net Kafka Producer</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"600236fb-9357-4a9e-88ce-82045dfd=
bfac-1409164991">
<h1 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaProducer-RedNotsupported"><span style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-loz=
enge-error">NOT SUPPORTED</span></strong></span></h1>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><strong>This feature is technically=
 available but Mesh platform team do not provide support for .NET</strong><=
/span></p>
<h1 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaProducer-StepstobuildaKafkaProducer:"><span=
 style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Steps to build a Kafka Producer:</s=
trong></span></h1>
<p>Any .Net API may be a .Net Kafka Producer. The ability to produce events=
 to Mesh Kafka is a capability of an API. In addition, other component type=
s (initially, .Net Kafka Listeners) may also be a .Net Kafka Producer.</p>
<p>You may be creating a new API, or adding a new capability to an existing=
 API.</p>
<h2 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaProducer-Prerequisites:">Prerequisites:</h2=
>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">.Net Kafka Producer API name is a=
pproved &amp; endorsed in confluence page: </span><a href=3D"https://conflu=
ence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/WDPREGO/API+Naming+Approvals" style=3D"text=
-decoration: none;text-align: left;" rel=3D"nofollow">API Naming Approvals<=
/a></li>
<li>A Bitbucket repo with the approved .Net Kafka Producer API name. Refer =
to <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/How+to+Cre=
ate+a+Bitbucket+Repository" rel=3D"nofollow">'How to Create a Bitbucket Rep=
ository'</a><span>&nbsp;</span>guide for creating one.</li>
<li>Your API must be a .Net API using the Kestrel container.</li>
<li>A Topic to produce messages to- see&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.=
srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Steps+to+build+a+Kafka+Topic?src=3Dcontextn=
avpagetreemode" rel=3D"nofollow">Steps to build a Kafka Topic</a>.</li>
<li>If you want to produce events to an existing topic, an approval from th=
e topic owner to produce to the topic. is needed.</li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 109=
0.0px;">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 44.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 1045.0px;">
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p>#</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p>Actions</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"Stepstobui=
lda.NetKafkaProducer-1"><strong>1</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaProducer-AddProducer"><strong>Add Producer&=
nbsp;</strong></h2>
<p>Add producer capability to the API component.</p>
<ul>
<li>Go to the component repository in cmd prompt.</li>
<li>Add producer capability by running 'enable' command and following the s=
creen prompts.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Add producer capability</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">Add Mesh Capability</b><span class=3D"collapse-sour=
ce expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-control-ic=
on icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand source</sp=
an></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: true; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midnig=
ht">mesh&nbsp;enable&nbsp;-a kafkaProducer</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"Stepstobui=
lda.NetKafkaProducer-2"><strong>2</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaProducer-GenerateCode"><strong>Generate Cod=
e&nbsp;</strong></h2>
<p>Generate code from the swagger:</p>
<ul>
<li>Place your latest approved swagger in your API repository directory.</l=
i>
<li>Run 'gencode' command.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Generate code from the swagger</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">Generate code from the swagger</b><span class=3D"co=
llapse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand=
-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand=
 source</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: true; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midnig=
ht">mesh gencode</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"Stepstobui=
lda.NetKafkaProducer-3"><strong>3</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaProducer-IncludeDependencies"><strong>Inclu=
de Dependencies</strong></h2>
<ul style=3D"text-align: left;">
<li>Include <strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">lib-mesh-platform=
-dotnet-kafkaproducer</span></strong> in your API .csproj file.</li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Include the Nuget Package that co=
rrespond to the Avro schema of the target topic.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Add other dotnet dependenc=
ies in your .csproj file.</span></strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">Example - Dependencies to include in .csproj file</=
b><span class=3D"collapse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><s=
pan class=3D"expand-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-c=
ontrol-text">Expand source</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wra=
pper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: xml; gutter: true; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midnigh=
t">&lt;ItemGroup&gt;
        &lt;!-- Check respective master branch of all following dependencie=
s for latest version--&gt;
        &lt;PackageReference Include=3D"Cap.Technolmgt.Pltf.Integ.Ref.Event=
.V1.Topic" Version=3D"1.0.0" /&gt;
=09=09&lt;PackageReference Include=3D"Lib.Mesh.Platform.Dotnet.KafkaProduce=
r" Version=3D"1.0.0" /&gt;
=09=09&lt;PackageReference Include=3D"Lib.Mesh.Platform.Dotnet.Kafka.Event.=
Helper" Version=3D"1.0.0" /&gt;
=09=09&lt;PackageReference Include=3D"Lib.Mesh.Platform.Dotnet.Support" Ver=
sion=3D"2.0.1" /&gt;
&lt;/ItemGroup&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"Stepstobui=
lda.NetKafkaProducer-4"><strong>4</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaProducer-CreateProducerInstance"><strong>Cr=
eate Producer&nbsp;</strong><strong>Instance</strong></h2>
<p>Create a producer instance :</p>
<ul>
<li>Westpac Mesh .Net Kafka producer library<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43=
,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"> provides a generic producer f=
actory which should be used to register Kafka producer instances</span></sp=
an>
<ul style=3D"text-align: left;">
<li>Developers can provide "HandleName", which is optional field. If not pr=
ovided, default handle is used</li>
<li>Based on the requirement, same handle can be used for multiple types of=
 producers.</li>
<li>For each unique handle name, factory will create a new IProducer&lt;byt=
e[], byte[]&gt; instance.&nbsp;</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">Register MeshKafkaProducer in API</b><span class=3D=
"collapse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"exp=
and-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Exp=
and source</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: c#; gutter: true; first-line: 1; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-th=
eme=3D"Midnight"> &nbsp;=09public static IServiceCollection AddKafkaProduce=
r(this IServiceCollection services)
    {
=09=09/*Step-1 Read logical topic name from appsettings.json*/
        var appSettings =3D new ConfigurationBuilder()
            .SetBasePath(Directory.GetCurrentDirectory())
            .AddJsonFile("appsettings.json")
            .Build();
        var referenceEventTopic =3D appSettings.GetValue&lt;string&gt;("ref=
erence.event.topic");

=09=09/*Step-2 Register Mesh Kafka Producer of reference event type*/
        services.AddMeshKafkaProducer&lt;ReferenceEvent&gt;();

=09=09/*Step-3 Register IMeshKafkaProducer &lt;ReferenceEvent&gt; with requ=
ired scope*/
        /*API Developers may choose to register MeshKafkaProducer as single=
ton, scoped or transient*/
        services.AddSingleton(sp =3D&gt; sp.GetRequiredService&lt;IMeshKafk=
aProducerFactory&lt;ReferenceEvent&gt;&gt;()
                                      .CreateProducer(referenceEventTopic, =
"ReferenceEventHandle"));

        return services;
    }</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"Stepstobui=
lda.NetKafkaProducer-5"><strong>5</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaProducer-Optional:CreatingMultipleevents"><=
strong>Optional: Creating Multiple events</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">To produce multiple events (with =
different record types) to multiple topics,&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"colo=
r: rgb(23,43,77);">register corresponding Kafka producer by providing their=
 topic names</span></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">Register Multiple MeshKafkaProducer in API</b><span=
 class=3D"collapse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span cla=
ss=3D"expand-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-=
text">Expand source</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"><=
/span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: c#; gutter: true; first-line: 1; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-th=
eme=3D"Midnight"> &nbsp;=09public static IServiceCollection AddKafkaProduce=
r(this IServiceCollection services)
    {
        var appSettings =3D new ConfigurationBuilder()
            .SetBasePath(Directory.GetCurrentDirectory())
            .AddJsonFile("appsettings.json")
            .Build();
        var referenceEventTopic1 =3D appSettings.GetValue&lt;string&gt;("re=
ference.event.topic1");
        var referenceEventTopic2 =3D appSettings.GetValue&lt;string&gt;("re=
ference.event.topic2");=20

 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;services.AddMeshKafkaProducer&lt;ReferenceEvent=
1&gt;();
  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; services.AddMeshKafkaProducer&lt;ReferenceEvent2&gt;=
();
=20
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;//API Developers may choose to register MeshKaf=
kaProducer as singleton, scoped or transient
        services.AddSingleton(sp =3D&gt; sp.GetRequiredService&lt;IMeshKafk=
aProducerFactory&lt;ReferenceEvent1&gt;&gt;()
                                      .CreateProducer(referenceEventTopic1,=
 "ReferenceEventHandle1"));
        services.AddSingleton(sp =3D&gt; sp.GetRequiredService&lt;IMeshKafk=
aProducerFactory&lt;ReferenceEvent2&gt;&gt;()
                                      .CreateProducer(referenceEventTopic2,=
 "ReferenceEventHandle2"));=20
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;return services;
    }</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"Stepstobui=
lda.NetKafkaProducer-6"><strong>6</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaProducer-UpdateProducerInstance"><strong>Up=
date Producer Instance</strong></h2>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span>MeshKafkaPoducer&lt;TValue&g=
t;</span> &nbsp;created in step 4 infers physical topic name from the logic=
al name of the topic - provided while registering the producer instance. In=
ject the instance of&nbsp; '<span>MeshKafkaPoducer&lt;TValue&gt;</span><cod=
e style=3D"text-align: left;">' </code>in your API implementation class and=
 invoke the 'ProduceEvent()' or 'ProduceEventAsync()'<span>&nbsp;</span>met=
hod in the producer instance created above to post an event to the configur=
ed topic.</span></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">Kafka Producer Dependency Injection</b><span class=
=3D"collapse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"=
expand-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">=
Expand source</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: c#; gutter: true; first-line: 1; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-th=
eme=3D"Midnight">public class KafkaProducerService : IKafkaProducerService
{
    private IMeshKafkaProducer&lt;ReferenceEvent&gt; _meshKafkaProducer;
    private ILogger _logger;

    /// &lt;summary&gt;
    /// Constructor
    /// &lt;/summary&gt;
    /// &lt;param name=3D"logger"Logger &lt;/param&gt;
    /// &lt;param name=3D"meshKafkaProducer"&gt;Injected meshKafkaProducer =
instance&lt;/param&gt;
    public KafkaProducerService(ILogger&lt;KafkaProducerService&gt; logger,
                                IMeshKafkaProducer&lt;ReferenceEvent&gt; me=
shKafkaProducer)
    {
        _logger =3D logger;
        _meshKafkaProducer =3D meshKafkaProducer;
    }
=09
    private async Task&lt;PublishEventResponse&gt; ProduceAsync(string xApp=
CorrelationId
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09, string xBrandSilo
 =09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09, string xOrganisationId
 =09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09, string xOriginatingSystemId
 =09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09, string xConsumerType
 =09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09, string xUserId
 =09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09, string xUserIdScheme
 =09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09, string xMessageId
 =09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09, PublishEventRequest publishEve=
ntRequest
 =09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09, CancellationToken cancellation=
Token)
    {
        PublishEventResponse response =3D null;
        var capEvent =3D BuildReferenceEvent(xAppCorrelationId, xBrandSilo,=
 xOrganisationId,
                                               xOriginatingSystemId, xConsu=
merType, xUserId,
                                               xUserIdScheme, xMessageId, p=
ublishEventRequest);

        try
        {
            Confluent.Kafka.DeliveryResult&lt;string, ReferenceEvent&gt; de=
liveryResult;
            deliveryResult =3D await _meshKafkaProducer.ProduceEventAsync(x=
MessageId, Guid.NewGuid().ToString(), capEvent, cancellationToken);

            response =3D new PublishEventResponse{ Data =3D new PublishEven=
tResponseData() };
            response.Data.Offset =3D deliveryResult?.Offset.Value;
            response.Data.Partition =3D deliveryResult?.Partition.Value;
            response.Data.Topic =3D deliveryResult?.Topic;
        }
        catch (Exception ex)
        {
            _logger.LogError($"Error while producing event : {ex}");
            throw;
        }
        return response;
    }=20
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"Stepstobui=
lda.NetKafkaProducer-7"><strong>7</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"Stepstobui=
lda.NetKafkaProducer-Optional:"><strong>Optional:</strong></h2><p>While mos=
t of the properties&nbsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">required for=
 connecting to Kafka brokers are auto-configured by the Westpac Mesh .Net K=
afka producer library, users can use <strong>kafka-producer.json </strong>t=
o supplement the producer config.</span></p><p><strong><span style=3D"color=
: rgb(23,43,77);">Note</span></strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"=
>: '</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">kafka-producer.json' shoul=
d not be used to inject any properties other than Kafka producer configurat=
ion or override Westpac Mesh injected properties. For a full list of Mesh i=
njected properties refer<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv=
.westpac.com.au/projects/WDPCOM/repos/lib-mesh-platform-dotnet-kafkaproduce=
r/browse/readme.md" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">readme.md</a>.=
</span></p><p><br></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"Stepstobui=
lda.NetKafkaProducer-8"><strong>8</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaProducer-BuildtheProducer"><strong>Build th=
e Producer</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>Go to the component repository in cmd prompt.</li>
<li>Execute 'mesh build' command</li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
