</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1409169286">Steps to build a .Net Kafka Listener</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"600236fb-9357-4a9e-88ce-82045dfd=
bfac-1409169286">
<h1 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-RedNotsupported"><span style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-loz=
enge-error">NOT SUPPORTED</span></strong></span></h1>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><strong>This feature is technically=
 available but Mesh platform team do not provide support for .NET</strong><=
/span></p>
<h2 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-Prerequisites:">Prerequisites:</h2=
>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">.Net Kafka Listener name is appro=
ved &amp; endorsed in confluence page: <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.we=
stpac.com.au/display/WDPREGO/Topic+Listener+Naming+Approvals" rel=3D"nofoll=
ow">Topic Listener Naming Approvals</a></span></li>
<li>A Bitbucket repo with the approved .Net Kafka Listener API name. Refer =
to <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/How+to+Cre=
ate+a+Bitbucket+Repository" rel=3D"nofollow">'How to Create a Bitbucket Rep=
ository'</a><span>&nbsp;</span>guide for creating one.</li>
<li>A Topic to consume messages from.</li>
<li>If you want to consume events from an existing topic, an approval from =
the topic owner is needed.</li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 186=
6.0px;">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 44.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 1821.0px;">
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p>#</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p>Actions&nbsp;</p>=
</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"Stepstobui=
lda.NetKafkaListener-1"><strong>1</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-GenerateCode"><strong>Generate Cod=
e</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>Get a repository created for Java <span class=3D"inline-comment-marker"=
 data-ref=3D"66bb2a8d-eb9f-4d0d-8c6d-ab5ffd98919d">listener. (In the follow=
ing steps, you will be converting it to .Net listener)&nbsp;</span></li>
<li>Update <strong>containerProfile</strong> to&nbsp;<strong>dotnet </stron=
g>in&nbsp;resources.yaml file&nbsp;</li>
<li>Delete pom.xml from repository.&nbsp;</li>
<li>Replace the <strong>swagger.yaml</strong> with swagger available <a hre=
f=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/wdp-cap-techno=
lmgt-pltf-integ-ref-dotnetkafka-v1-listener/browse/swagger.yaml" class=3D"e=
xternal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">here</a></li>
<li>Replace the <strong>title</strong> and&nbsp;<strong>basePath</strong> w=
ith your listener api name</li>
<li>Generate code using swagger.yaml and 'mesh gencode' command to get boil=
erplate dotnet api code,</li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">mesh gencode</b><span class=3D"collapse-source expa=
nd-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-control-icon icon=
">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand source</span></sp=
an><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: true; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midnig=
ht">mesh gencode</pre>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Remove "/Attributes", "/Controlle=
rs", "/Models" directories from the generated code. Please note HealthCheck=
 &amp; ProcessEvent Controller are provided by platform library.</span></li=
>
</ul>
<p>For further help on the commands refer to Mesh Developer tools<span>&nbs=
p;</span><a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Mesh=
+Developer+Tools" rel=3D"nofollow">documentation</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Note</strong>: mesh gencode for dotnet listener is not available=
 as of now, so generate code for listener as a normal API, and then remove =
unnecessary files from the generated code</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"Stepstobui=
lda.NetKafkaListener-2"><strong>2</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-Remove/Replace-Refactor"><strong>R=
emove/Replace - Refactor</strong></h2>
<p>The previous step creates a .NET <span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" d=
ata-ref=3D"cc11ccd8-052d-46dc-94ed-9b79afa0cb29">listener</span> implementa=
tion. Follow the below steps to add a required dependency.</p>
<ul>
<li>Add reference to <strong>Lib.Mesh.Platform.Dotnet.KafkaListener</strong=
> in your .csproj file</li>
<li>Add reference to topic library for which listener will consume events.<=
/li>
<li>Verify/Ensure required topic build process has published nuget package =
published. You can also search the nuget package using Nuget Package Manage=
r of Visual Studio=20
<ul>
<li>Add artifactory source: Westpac MESH Artifactory source&nbsp; <a class=
=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://artifactory.srv.westpac.com.au/artifacto=
ry/api/nuget/a0072b-wdp-nuget" rel=3D"nofollow">https://artifactory.srv.wes=
tpac.com.au/artifactory/api/nuget/a0072b-wdp-nuget</a></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">Example - Dependencies to include in .csproj file</=
b><span class=3D"collapse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><s=
pan class=3D"expand-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-c=
ontrol-text">Expand source</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wra=
pper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: xml; gutter: true; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midnigh=
t">&lt;ItemGroup&gt;=20
        &lt;!-- Check respective master branch of all following dependencie=
s for latest version--&gt; &nbsp; =09
=09    &lt;PackageReference Include=3D"Cap.Technolmgt.Pltf.Integ.Ref.Event.=
V1.Topic" Version=3D"1.0.0" /&gt; &lt;!-- Replace Topic name with required =
topic name (case sensitive) --&gt;
=09=09&lt;PackageReference Include=3D"Lib.Mesh.Platform.Dotnet.Kafka.Event.=
Helper" Version=3D"1.0.0" /&gt;
=09=09&lt;PackageReference Include=3D"Lib.Mesh.Platform.Dotnet.Support" Ver=
sion=3D"2.0.1" /&gt;=20
&lt;/ItemGroup&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div><br>
<ul>
<li>Add a <strong>Listener </strong>class&nbsp; (for example: <a href=3D"ht=
tps://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/wdp-cap-technolmgt-pl=
tf-integ-ref-dotnetkafka-v1-listener/browse/src/Cap.Technolmgt.Pltf.Integ.R=
ef.Dotnetkafka.V1/Listener/Implementation/ReferenceEventListener.cs" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">ReferenceEventListener</a>) and impleme=
nt <strong>AbstractMeshKafkaListener&lt;T&gt; </strong>class (T will be Eve=
nt Type from the topic library)</li>
<li>Implement your business logic in "abstract async" <strong>HandleMessage=
Async&nbsp;</strong>method. T<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">his<span=
> </span></span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><strong>HandleMessage=
Async</strong></span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">&nbsp;method get=
s invoked when the Kafka container receives an event.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Please refer <a href=3D"https://bi=
tbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-integ=
-ref-dotnetkafka-v1-listener/browse" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollo=
w">Reference Event Listener</a> for more details</span></p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"Stepstobui=
lda.NetKafkaListener-3"><strong>3</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-ImplementErrorHandling"><strong>Im=
plement Error Handling</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>If the event processing encounters an exception that is retry-able (lik=
e technical exceptions), you can retry the event by wrapping the exception =
in an instance of <strong>MeshKafkaRetryableException</strong> and throwing=
 back to the container.</li>
<li>If the event processing encounters an exception that is not retry-able =
(like business exceptions), you should wrap the exception in an instance of=
 <strong>MeshKafkaNonRetryableException</strong> and throwback to the conta=
iner.</li>
<li>By default, any unhandled exceptions that are encountered while process=
ing the event are treated as non-retry-able.</li>
<li>Optionally,&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projec=
ts/WDPCOM/repos/lib-westpac-digital-platform-retrycontext-schema/browse/src=
/main/schema/RetryContext.schema.json" class=3D"external-link" style=3D"tex=
t-decoration: none;" rel=3D"nofollow">RetryContext<span>&nbsp;</span></a>-t=
he placeholder for the exception details returned from API invocation, retr=
y metadata as a key-value pair, can be provided while instantiating <strong=
>MeshKafkaRetryableException</strong>/<strong>MeshKafkaNonRetryableExceptio=
n</strong>.</li>
<li>Retry context provided in the previous step is populated in the <strong=
>KafkaRecordHeaders</strong> while publishing the event to DLT. This contex=
t information can be used while processing failed events from the DLT.</li>
</ul>
<p>Full implementation of error handling can be found in the<span>&nbsp;</s=
pan><a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/wdp-=
cap-technolmgt-pltf-integ-ref-dotnetkafka-v1-listener/browse" class=3D"exte=
rnal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">reference listener</a>.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">Sample Error Handling</b><span class=3D"collapse-so=
urce expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-control-=
icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand source</=
span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: true; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midnig=
ht">public override async Task HandleMessageAsync(ConsumeResult&lt;string, =
ReferenceEvent&gt; consumerRecord, CancellationToken cancellationToken)
    {
        PropagatePayloadResponse loadTestApiResponse =3D null;
        try
        {
            cancellationToken.ThrowIfCancellationRequested();       =20
            PropagatePayloadRequest propagatePayloadRequest =3D BuildReques=
tEntity(consumerRecord, cancellationToken);
            loadTestApiResponse =3D await GetPropagateResponseAsync(propaga=
tePayloadRequest, consumerRecord).ConfigureAwait(false);
        }
      =20
        catch (Exception exception)
        {
            _logger.LogError($"ReferenceEventListener - Encountered excepti=
on - ExceptionDetail: {exception}");
            throw;
        }
    }

private async Task&lt;PropagatePayloadResponse&gt; GetPropagateResponseAsyn=
c(PropagatePayloadRequest propagatePayloadRequest, ConsumeResult&lt;string,=
 ReferenceEvent&gt; consumerRecord)
    {
        MeshLoadTestApiResponse meshLoadTestApiResponse =3D null;
        PropagatePayloadResponse consumerResponse;
        try
        {
            MeshLoadTestApiRequest meshLoadTestApiRequest =3D _meshLoadTest=
ApiMapper.GetMeshLoadTestApiRequest(propagatePayloadRequest);
            using (var httpClient =3D _meshHttpClientFactory.CreateMeshHttp=
Client())
            {
                var httpResponseMessage =3D await httpClient.PostAsJson(_me=
shApiOptions.Value.LoadTestApiPayloadEndpoint, meshLoadTestApiRequest).Conf=
igureAwait(false);

                if (!httpResponseMessage.IsSuccessStatusCode)
                    HandleException(consumerRecord.Message.Key, httpRespons=
eMessage);

                meshLoadTestApiResponse =3D await httpResponseMessage.ReadC=
ontentAsAsync&lt;MeshLoadTestApiResponse&gt;().ConfigureAwait(false);
            }
            consumerResponse =3D _meshLoadTestApiMapper.GetPropagatePayload=
Response(meshLoadTestApiResponse);
        }
        catch (Exception ex)
        {
            _logger.LogError($"Error GetPropagateResponseAsync. Exception D=
etails: {ex}");
            throw;
        }
        _logger.LogTrace("End GetPropagateResponseAsync.");
        return consumerResponse;
    }

private void HandleException(string key, HttpResponseMessage httpResponseMe=
ssage)
    {
        /* Throw a MeshKafkaServiceUnavailableException if any of the servi=
ces are not responsive
         * DISCLAIMER: Throw this ONLY if you want to pause the container a=
fter exhausting the retries configured
         * by max.retry.attempts property - This will also prevent DLT comm=
it and publish */
        if (httpResponseMessage.StatusCode =3D=3D HttpStatusCode.BadGateway=
 || httpResponseMessage.StatusCode =3D=3D HttpStatusCode.ServiceUnavailable=
)
        {
            throw new MeshKafkaServiceUnavailableException("SERVICE_HEALTH_=
CHECK_CALLBACK", "Backend Service Unavailable", BuildRetryContext(GetErrorC=
odes(httpResponseMessage)), null);
        }

        /* Even though '429-Too many requests' is a client exception, it is=
 recommended to throw it as a retry-able exception.*/
        if (httpResponseMessage.StatusCode =3D=3D HttpStatusCode.TooManyReq=
uests || httpResponseMessage.StatusCode =3D=3D HttpStatusCode.InternalServe=
rError)
        {
            throw new MeshKafkaRetryableException(key, "Failed to process m=
essage", BuildRetryContext(GetErrorCodes(httpResponseMessage)), null);
        }
        else
        {
            throw new MeshKafkaNonRetryableException(key, "Failed to proces=
s message", BuildRetryContext(GetErrorCodes(httpResponseMessage)), null);
        }
    }
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=
=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-4"><strong>4</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-ConfigureRetryProperties"><strong>=
Configure Retry Properties</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">MeshKafkaListener c</span><span s=
tyle=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">an retry an event on an exception from the l=
istener implementation using a simple retry and exponential back-off policy=
.</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Wrap any exception you want to re=
try as</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"> <strong>MeshKafkaRetrya=
bleException</strong> </span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">and any =
exception you don't want to retry as</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,=
77);"> <strong>MeshKafkaNonRetryableException</strong></span><span style=3D=
"color: rgb(23,43,77);">.</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">On exhausting all retries, the ev=
ent is published to dead letter topic with any retry context passed in the =
exception.</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">By default, retry functionality i=
s configured with the following values. One can override default values by =
defining custom values in</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">&nbsp=
;'<strong>kafka-consumer.json'</strong><span>&nbsp;</span>file&nbsp;</span>=
<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">with an appropriate key.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
</div>
<div id=3D"expander-152520981" class=3D"expand-container">
<div role=3D"heading" aria-level=3D"6" id=3D"expander-control-152520981" cl=
ass=3D"expand-control"><button type=3D"button" id=3D"expand-button-15252098=
1" class=3D"aui-button aui-button-link aui-button-link-icon-text" aria-expa=
nded=3D"true" aria-controls=3D"expander-content-152520981"><span class=3D"e=
xpand-icon aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-chevron-down" aria-hidden=
=3D"true"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text conf-macro-render">Defa=
ult retry configurations</span></button>
</div>
<div role=3D"region" id=3D"expander-content-152520981" class=3D"expand-cont=
ent" aria-labelledby=3D"expand-button-152520981">
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable" data-mce-resize=3D"false">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><span style=3D"col=
or: rgb(23,43,77);">Key</span></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTh">Description</th>
<th style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTh">default value</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>retry.initial.interval</code></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">The 'initialInterval' value in milli-sec</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">100</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>retry.multiplier</code></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">The 'multiplier' value</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">2</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>retry.max.interval</code></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">maximum backoff time in milli-sec</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">30000</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>max.retry.attempts</code></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">The limit to the number of attempts&nbsp;</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">3</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>The defaults above result in the following retry behavior (assuming retr=
yable exceptions):</p>
<ul>
<li>after the first attempt fails, backoff will wait 100ms before retry</li=
>
<li>after the second attempt fails, backoff will wait 200ms before retry</l=
i>
<li>after the third attempt fails, the event goes to DLT</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=
=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-5"><strong>5</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=
=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-Optional:"><strong>Optional:</strong></h=
2><p>While most of the properties&nbsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);=
">required for connecting to Kafka brokers are auto-configured by Mesh Kafk=
a listener library, users can use&nbsp;<strong>kafka-consumer.json<span>&nb=
sp;</span></strong>to supplement the consumer config.</span></p><p><strong>=
<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Note</span></strong><span style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(23,43,77);">: '</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">kafka-=
consumer.json 'should not be used to inject any properties other than Kafka=
 consumer configuration or override Mesh injected properties. For a full li=
st of Mesh injected properties refer<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=3D"https://b=
itbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDPCOM/repos/lib-mesh-platform-dotnet-=
kafkalistener/browse/readme.md" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">re=
adme.md</a>.</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=
=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-6"><strong>6</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=
=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-Optional:.1"><strong>Optional:</strong><=
/h2><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Every consumer is bundled with=
 a Kafka producer to publish failed events to the Dead letter topic. All th=
e properties for the DLT publisher are injected by the listener library, us=
ers can use&nbsp;<strong>kafka-producer.json<span>&nbsp;</span></strong>to =
supplement the DLT publisher config.</span></p><p><strong><span style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(23,43,77);">Note</span></strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77=
);">: '</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">kafka-producer.json 'sh=
ould not be used to inject any properties other than Kafka producer configu=
ration for DLT publishing or override Mesh injected properties. For a full =
list of Mesh injected properties refer<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=3D"https:/=
/bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDPCOM/repos/lib-mesh-platform-dotne=
t-kafkaproducer/browse/readme.md" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">=
readme.md</a>.</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=
=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-7"><strong>7</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=
=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-PublishandTest"><strong>Publish and Test=
</strong></h2><p>Publishing a message&nbsp; using 'testproducer' utility fo=
r testing</p>
<ul>
<li>During development, it might be useful to publish a message to the topi=
c in a dev environment, which could be consumed by the listener locally / l=
istener in dev environment for testing the functionality.</li>
<li>Mesh provides a 'testproducer' utility to support publishing an event.<=
/li>
<li>This test producer is a standalone component, developed solely to publi=
sh events, that can be run independently of the listener.</li>
<li>Refer to&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.=
westpac.com.au/projects/WDPCOM/repos/lib-westpac-digital-platform-kafka-tes=
tproducer/browse/readme.md" rel=3D"nofollow">kafka-testproducer</a><span>&n=
bsp;</span>for running the utility</li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=
=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-8"><strong>8</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-FunctionalTestingtheListener"><str=
ong>Functional Testing the Listener</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>Westpac Mesh uses canary deployment (a deployment in which the new vers=
ion of the deployable is tested before beginning a rolling update) to ensur=
e safe application rollout to an environment. As a listener can only be inv=
oked by publishing an event to a topic and the old version of the listener =
was already subscribed to the topic, it is difficult to test the functional=
ity of a new version of a Kafka listener to be promoted without causing an =
outage.</li>
<li><span>To get around this problem Mesh .Net Kafka listener library provi=
des an HTTP endpoint that invokes the <strong>HandleMessageAsync</strong> m=
ethod in the .Net Kafka listener implementation.</span></li>
<li><span>Similar to the newman test suite used for testing the API functio=
nality, developers can include&nbsp;</span><span>their functional tests in =
the newman suite that gets executed during the canary deployment.</span></l=
i>
<li><span>These tests call <strong>HandleMessageAsync</strong> synchronousl=
y, and so success or any errors (Exceptions) will be reported in the HTTP r=
esponse.</span></li>
<li><span>If any of the assertion in the test suite fails, the deployment w=
ill be failed and the updated version will not be rolled in.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Note:&nbsp;<span style=3D"=
color: rgb(51,51,51);">The functional tests invoke live endpoints of downst=
ream systems in a given environment. This could result in data integrity is=
sues if your test causes your listener to invoke any non-idempotent back en=
d systems.</span></span></strong></p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=
=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-9"><strong>9</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-BuildtheListener"><strong>Build th=
e Listener</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>Go to the component repository in cmd prompt.</li>
<li>Execute 'mesh build' command</li>
</ul><br>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">mesh build</b><span class=3D"collapse-source expand=
-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-control-icon icon">=
&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand source</span></span=
><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: true; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midnig=
ht">mesh build</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=
=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-10"><strong>10</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-DeploytheListener"><strong>Deploy =
the Listener</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>Go to the component repository in cmd prompt.</li>
<li>Execute 'mesh deploy' command and provide the intended environment, bui=
ld number.</li>
</ul><br>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">mesh deploy</b><span class=3D"collapse-source expan=
d-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-control-icon icon"=
>&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand source</span></spa=
n><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: true; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midnig=
ht">mesh deploy -e &lt;environment to deploy&gt; -b &lt;build number of the=
 artifact to deploy&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=
=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-11"><strong>11</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=
=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-.NetKafkaListenerandSwimlaneSupport"><st=
rong>.Net Kafka Listener and Swimlane Support</strong></h2><p>Just like a M=
esh API, .Net Kafka listener API supports virtual swimlanes. The process to=
 enroll, deploy, and undeploy a swimlane is the same as that of a normal AP=
I. Refer to Mesh Developer tools<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=3D"https://confl=
uence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Mesh+Developer+Tools" rel=3D"nofollow=
">documentation</a>&nbsp;for swimlane operations.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=
=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-12"><strong>12</strong></h2></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-TestingListenerCodeLocally:"><stro=
ng>Testing Listener Code Locally:</strong></h2>
<p>A listener can be run from on your local workstation with a little bit o=
f configuration.</p>
<p>All the ACLs required to consume events from a topic are configured by t=
he deploy pipeline. Hence to run locally, as a prerequisite, your listener =
code should be deployed to dev1<strong>&nbsp;at least</strong>&nbsp;once.</=
p>
<ul>
<li>Copy the entries from the logs of 'Kafka - Configure Access' step in th=
e dev deploy pipeline.</li>
<li>Create a file named '<strong>wdp-kafka-secrets.json</strong>' in secret=
s/local folder and copy the 'username' and 'password' properties from the l=
ogs of 'Kafka - Configure Access' step in the dev deploy pipeline.</li>
<li>Contact BAU for password to connect to dev environment and place it in =
the 'password' property of&nbsp; 'wdp-kafka-secrets.json'.</li>
<li>Run listener locally like any other API</li>
<li>Produce an event locally, listener should receive and process the event=
</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;"><strong>Note:</strong></p>
<ul style=3D"text-align: left;">
<li>Currently, Listener can be tested from local machine, provided that top=
ic is available on enterprise confluent (non confluent cloud).</li>
</ul>
<div id=3D"expander-378427545" class=3D"expand-container">
<div role=3D"heading" aria-level=3D"6" id=3D"expander-control-378427545" cl=
ass=3D"expand-control"><button type=3D"button" id=3D"expand-button-37842754=
