<h2 id=3D"Stepstobuilda.NetKafkaListener-ContactsforassistancewithWestpacMe=
shEngagementandServiceDeskTeams:"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><str=
ong>Contacts for assistance with Westpac Mesh Engagement and Service Desk T=
eams:</strong></span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Westpac Mesh Engagement:&nbsp;<a href=3D"mailto:WDPEngagement@westpac.c=
om.au" style=3D"text-decoration: none;" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofo=
llow">WDPEngagement@westpac.com.au</a></li>
<li>Westpac Mesh Service Desk:&nbsp;<a href=3D"mailto:WDPSupport@westpac.co=
m.au" class=3D"external-link" style=3D"text-decoration: none;" rel=3D"nofol=
low">WDPSupport@westpac.com.au</a></li>
</ul>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1409169950">.Net Kafka Event Helper Library</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"600236fb-9357-4a9e-88ce-82045dfd=
bfac-1409169950">
<h1 id=3D"id-.NetKafkaEventHelperLibrary-RedNotsupported"><span style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-loz=
enge-error">NOT SUPPORTED</span></strong></span></h1>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><strong>This feature is technically=
 available but Mesh platform team do not provide support for .NET</strong><=
/span></p>
<p>This library has a set of useful classes to help with Mesh Kafka Events.=
</p>
<h1 id=3D"id-.NetKafkaEventHelperLibrary-EventUtils"><u>EventUtils</u></h1>
<p>This class contains a set of utility methods to help with conversion of =
Date, Time and Timestamp from Swagger format to Avro format and vice-versa.=
</p>
<p>The following utility methods are available:</p>
<p><span><em>AvroDateToSwaggerDate</em> </span>- converts AVRO Logical Type=
 Date to RFC3339 format Date.<span>&nbsp;</span><em>[ eg: 18262&nbsp;=E2=86=
=92 2020-01-01 ]</em></p>
<p><span><em>SwaggerDateToAvroDate</em> </span>- converts RFC3339 format Da=
te to AVRO Logical Type Date.&nbsp;<em>[ eg: 2021-01-01 =E2=86=92 18628 ]</=
em></p>
<p><span><em>AvroTimeToSwaggerTime</em> </span>- converts AVRO Logical Type=
 Time-Millis to RFC3339 format Time.&nbsp;<em>[ eg: 73220202 =E2=86=92 20:2=
0:20.202 ]</em></p>
<p><span><em>SwaggerTimeToAvroTime</em> </span>- converts RFC3339 format Ti=
me to AVRO Logical Type Time-Millis.&nbsp;<em>[ eg: 12:00:00 =E2=86=92 4320=
0000 ]</em></p>
<p><span><em>AvroTimestampToSwaggerDateTime</em> </span>- converts AVRO Log=
ical Type Timestamp-Millis to RFC3339 format DateTime.&nbsp;<em>[ eg: 0&nbs=
p;=E2=86=92&nbsp;1970-01-01T00:00:00Z ]</em></p>
<p><span><em>SwaggerDateTimeToAvroTimestamp</em> </span>- converts RFC3339 =
format DateTime to AVRO Logical Type Timestamp-Millis.&nbsp;<em>[ eg:&nbsp;=
2020-01-01T20:02:20.020Z =E2=86=92&nbsp;1577908940020 ]</em></p>
<h2 id=3D"id-.NetKafkaEventHelperLibrary-Howtouse">How to use</h2>
<p>You can add the following compile-time dependency in your .csproj:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>Adding EventHelper Reference to .csproj</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: xml; gutter: false; theme: Midnight" data-theme=3D"Midnight">&lt;ItemGrou=
p&gt;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;PackageReference Include=3D"Lib.Mesh.Platfo=
rm.Dotnet.Kafka.Event.Helper" Version=3D"1.0.0" /&gt;
=09=09&lt;!-- Check the Lib.Mesh.Platform.Dotnet.Kafka.Event.Helper.csproj =
file in Master branch for latest version--&gt;=20
&lt;/ItemGroup&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"id-.NetKafkaEventHelperLibrary-UsingEventUtils">Using EventUtils<=
/h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>Using EventUtils.cs</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: c#; gutter: true; theme: Midnight" data-theme=3D"Midnight">// converts RF=
C3339 format Date to AVRO Logical Type Date. [ eg: 2021-01-01 =E2=86=92 186=
28 ]
string dateToConvert =3D DateTime.Now.ToString(@"yyyy-MM-dd");
int avroDate =3D EventUtils.SwaggerDateToAvroDate(dateToConvert);
&nbsp;
// converts RFC3339 format Time to AVRO Logical Type Time-Millis. [ eg: 12:=
00:00 =E2=86=92 43200000 ]
string dateToConvert =3D DateTime.Now.ToString(@"HH:mm:ss.fff");
int avroTime =3D EventUtils.SwaggerTimeToAvroTime(dateToConvert);

// converts RFC3339 format DateTime to AVRO Logical Type Timestamp-Millis. =
[ eg: 2020-01-01T20:02:20.020Z =E2=86=92 1577908940020 ]
string dateToConvert =3D DateTime.Now.ToString(@"yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ss.fff");
long avroDateTime =3D EventUtils.SwaggerDateTimeToAvroTimestamp(dateToConve=
rt);
&nbsp;
// converts AVRO Logical Type Date to RFC3339 format Date. [ eg: 18262 =E2=
=86=92 2020-01-01 ]
string swaggerDate =3D EventUtils.AvroDateToSwaggerDate(123);
&nbsp;
// converts AVRO Logical Type Time-Millis to RFC3339 format Time. [ eg: 732=
20202 =E2=86=92 20:20:20.202 ]
string swaggerTime =3D EventUtils.AvroTimeToSwaggerTime(12345678);
&nbsp;
// converts AVRO Logical Type Timestamp-Millis to RFC3339 format DateTime. =
[ eg: 0 =E2=86=92 1970-01-01T00:00:00Z ]
string swaggerDateTime =3D EventUtils.AvroTimestampToSwaggerDateTime(123456=
789);</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h2 style=3D"text-align: left;" id=3D"id-.NetKafkaEventHelperLibrary-Refere=
nces">References</h2>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;"><a href=3D"https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc33=
39" rel=3D"nofollow" class=3D"external-link">https://tools.ietf.org/html/rf=
c3339</a><span>&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;"><a href=3D"https://avro.apache.org/docs/1.9.=
2/spec.html#Logical+Types" rel=3D"nofollow" class=3D"external-link">https:/=
/avro.apache.org/docs/1.9.2/spec.html#Logical+Types</a></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1696661602">Steps to build a Kafka Stream Processor</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"600236fb-9357-4a9e-88ce-82045dfd=
bfac-1696661602">
<h1 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-RedNotsupported"><span style=3D=
"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-=
lozenge-error">NOT SUPPORTED</span></strong></span></h1>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><strong>This feature is has been re=
tired and is no longer supported.</strong></span></p>
<h1 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcess=
or:"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Steps to build a Kafka St=
ream Processor:</strong></span></h1>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"sectionColumnWrapper">
<div class=3D"sectionMacro">
<div class=3D"sectionMacroRow">
<div class=3D"columnMacro" style=3D"width:70%;min-width:70%;max-width:70%;"=
>
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-Prerequisites:">Prerequisites:<=
/h2>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Kafka Stream Processor name&nbsp;=
 is approved &amp; endorsed on the confluence page: <a href=3D"/display/WDP=
REGO/Topic+Listener+Naming+Approvals">Topic Listener Naming Approvals</a></=
span></li>
<li>A Bitbucket repo with the approved Kafka Stream Processor name. Refer t=
o the <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/How+to+=
Create+a+Bitbucket+Repository" rel=3D"nofollow">'How to Create a Bitbucket =
Repository'</a> guide.</li>
<li>A Topic(s) to consume messages from.</li>
<li>If you want to consume events from an existing topic, approval from the=
 topic owner is needed.</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 95.=
797%;">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 2.0985%;">
<col style=3D"width: 38.4154%;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">#</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Actions&nbsp;</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-1"><=
strong>1</strong></h2></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-InitialiseStreamProcessorCompon=
ent"><strong>Initialise Stream Processor Component</strong></h2>
<p>Initialise Kafka Stream Processor component repository using Mesh Dev to=
ols</p>
<ul>
<li>Clone the Bitbucket repo of your stream processor and switch to a featu=
re branch&nbsp;</li>
<li>Open Mesh developer tools, provide the swagger/open API, and run 'genco=
de' command</li>
<li>Follow the screen prompts and generate the skeleton code for the Stream=
 Processor component</li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>mesh gencode</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">mesh ge=
ncode</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>For further help on the commands refer to Mesh Developer tools <a href=
=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Mesh+Developer+Tools=
" rel=3D"nofollow">documentation</a>.</p>
<p><br></p>
<div id=3D"expander-525872086" class=3D"expand-container">
<div role=3D"heading" aria-level=3D"6" id=3D"expander-control-525872086" cl=
ass=3D"expand-control"><button type=3D"button" id=3D"expand-button-52587208=
6" class=3D"aui-button aui-button-link aui-button-link-icon-text" aria-expa=
nded=3D"true" aria-controls=3D"expander-content-525872086"><span class=3D"e=
xpand-icon aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-chevron-down" aria-hidden=
=3D"true"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text conf-macro-render">See =
Example:</span></button>
</div>
<div role=3D"region" id=3D"expander-content-525872086" class=3D"expand-cont=
ent" aria-labelledby=3D"expand-button-525872086">
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"268" src=3D"9115bcbf78f4bab690fad9fd6440303cd5a311b542d783b1bcd3ff43e2=
30a9d5" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1696661602/image-2024-5-16_=
23-48-19.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1715869996130&amp;api=3Dv2"=
 data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1696661591"=
 data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment=
" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image-2024-5-16_23-48-19.png" data-=
base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-con=
tent-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1696661602" da=
ta-linked-resource-container-version=3D"8" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></=
p>
</div>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-2"><=
strong>2</strong></h2></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-Impl=
ementStreamsTopology"><strong>Implement Streams Topology</strong></h2><p><s=
trong><br><br><em>Note: We recommend using the<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,=
43,77);"><span>&nbsp;</span></span><a class=3D"external-link" style=3D"text=
-align: left;" href=3D"https://docs.confluent.io/platform/current/streams/d=
eveloper-guide/dsl-api.html#streams-dsl" rel=3D"nofollow">Kafka Streams DSL=
</a><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span>&nbsp;</span>rather than<sp=
an>&nbsp;</span></span><a class=3D"external-link" style=3D"text-align: left=
;" href=3D"https://docs.confluent.io/platform/current/streams/developer-gui=
de/processor-api.html#kstreams-processor-api" rel=3D"nofollow">Kafka Stream=
s Processor API</a></em></strong></p><p>The previous step creates a skeleto=
n implementation of the API based on the swagger/open API specification<spa=
n>.</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Implement<span>&nbsp;</span></spa=
n><code style=3D"text-align: left;">TopologyBuilder</code><span style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(23,43,77);"><span>&nbsp;</span>interface to provide the streams to=
pology using the </span><code style=3D"text-align: left;">buildTopology()</=
code><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,=
77);"><span>&nbsp;</span>method for your Streams processor.<br>
 Check <a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/w=
dp-inf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-meshrefstreamprocsr-v1-streamprocessor/b=
rowse/src/main/java/au/com/westpac/inf/bnkng/resrcitm/logclitcmpnt/meshrefs=
treamprocsr/v1/ReferenceStreamsTopologyBuilder.java" class=3D"external-link=
" rel=3D"nofollow">reference stream processor</a> for a sample implementati=
on.</span></span></li>
<li><p><em>MeshStreamProcessorApplication </em>class provided the 'lib-mesh=
-platform-streamprocessor' abstracts the KafkaStreams creation and streams =
configuration injection.&nbsp;<br>
 All stream processors hosted in Mesh should create an instance of the <em>=
MeshStreamProcessorApplication&nbsp;</em> with the topology builder implent=
ed in the above step and invoke the&nbsp;</p><em>initialize() </em>method o=
n the instance of the <em>MeshStreamProcessorApplication.&nbsp;<br></em>One=
 can take advantage of the init() of the BootStrap.java created by the genc=
ode to bootstrap the creation of the <em>MeshStreamProcessorApplication&nbs=
p;&nbsp; </em>instance.<em><br></em><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">C=
heck <a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/wdp=
-inf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-meshrefstreamprocsr-v1-streamprocessor/bro=
wse/src/main/java/au/com/westpac/inf/bnkng/resrcitm/logclitcmpnt/meshrefstr=
eamprocsr/v1/Bootstrap.java" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">refer=
ence stream processor</a> for a sample implementation.</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">For graceful shutdown of the stre=
aming application, one should implement the<em> destroy() </em>of the<em> M=
eshStreamProcessorApplication</em>&nbsp; instance which<br>
 would be invoked before the shutdown of the streaming application.&nbsp;<b=
r></span>One can take advantage of the destroy() of the BootStrap.java crea=
ted by the gencode to bootstrap the creation of the <em>MeshStreamProcessor=
Application&nbsp;&nbsp; </em>instance.<em><br></em><span style=3D"color: rg=
b(23,43,77);">Check <a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/project=
s/WDP/repos/wdp-inf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-meshrefstreamprocsr-v1-stre=
amprocessor/browse/src/main/java/au/com/westpac/inf/bnkng/resrcitm/logclitc=
mpnt/meshrefstreamprocsr/v1/Bootstrap.java" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"=
nofollow">reference stream processor</a> for a sample implementation.</span=
></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-3"><=
strong>3</strong></h2></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-UnitTesttheStreamsTopology"><st=
rong>Unit Test the Streams Topology</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>Using the <em>TopologyTestDriver</em> class provided in the<em> kafka-t=
est-utils</em> library, one can unit test the streams topology.<br><span st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Check <a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpa=
c.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/wdp-inf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-meshrefstre=
amprocsr-v1-streamprocessor/browse/src/test/java/au/com/westpac/inf/bnkng/r=
esrcitm/logclitcmpnt/meshrefstreamprocsr/v1/ReferenceStreamsTopologyBuilder=
Test.java" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">reference stream proces=
sor</a> for a sample implementation.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-4"><=
strong>4</strong></h2></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-Opti=
onal:"><strong>Optional:</strong></h2><p>While most of the properties&nbsp;=
<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">required for connecting to Kafka brok=
ers, initialising the streams are auto-configured by Mesh Kafka stream proc=
essor library, users can use <strong>streams-config.properties </strong>to =
supplement the streams config.</span></p><p><strong><span style=3D"color: r=
gb(23,43,77);">Note</span></strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">: =
'</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">streams-config.properties 'sh=
ould not be used to inject any properties other than Kafka Streams configur=
ation or override Mesh injected properties.</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-5"><=
strong>5</strong></h2></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-Publ=
ishandTest"><strong>Publish and Test</strong></h2><p>Publishing a message u=
sing 'testproducer' utility for testing</p>
<ul>
<li>During development, it might be useful to publish a message to the topi=
c in a dev environment, which could be consumed by the stream processor loc=
ally / stream processor in dev environment for testing the functionality.</=
li>
<li>Mesh provides a 'testproducer' utility to support publishing an event.<=
/li>
<li>This test producer is a standalone component, developed solely to publi=
sh events, that can be run independently of the listener.</li>
<li>Refer to&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/=
WDPCOM/repos/lib-westpac-digital-platform-kafka-testproducer/browse/readme.=
md" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">kafka-testproducer</a> for run=
ning the utility</li>
</ul><p><br></p><p><br></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-6"><=
strong>6</strong></h2></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-BuildtheStreamprocessor"><stron=
g>Build the Stream processor</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>Go to the component repository in cmd prompt.</li>
<li>Execute 'mesh build' command</li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>mesh build</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">mesh bu=
ild</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
</div><p><br></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-7"><=
strong>7</strong></h2></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-DeploytheListener"><strong>Depl=
oy the Listener</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>Go to the component repository in cmd prompt.</li>
<li>Execute 'mesh deploy' command and provide the intended environment, bui=
ld number.</li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>mesh deploy</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">mesh de=
ploy -e &lt;environment to deploy&gt; -n &lt;build number of the artifact t=
o deploy&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
</div><p><br></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-8"><=
strong>8</strong></h2></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-StreamprocessorandSwimlaneSuppo=
rt"><strong>Stream processor and Swimlane Support</strong></h2>
<p>Just like a Mesh Kafka listener, Kafka Stream Processors in Mesh support=
s virtual swimlanes.The process to enroll, deploy, and undeploy a swimlane =
is the same as that of a normal API. Refer to Mesh Developer tools <a href=
=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Mesh+Developer+Tools=
" rel=3D"nofollow">documentation</a>&nbsp;for swimlane operations.&nbsp;&nb=
sp;</p>
<h4 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-Important:"><strong><em>Importa=
nt:&nbsp;<br><br></em></strong></h4>
<p>Mesh uses streams <a href=3D"https://docs.confluent.io/platform/current/=
streams/javadocs/javadoc/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/Transformer.html"=
 class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Transformer</a> to add swimlane s=
upport for the Streams Processor. The Mesh Stream processor support library=
 provides <em>SwimlaneTransformer,<br></em>an implementation of the Transfo=
rmer interface, which wraps the swimlane routing logic.&nbsp;<br><strong><e=
m>Each source</em></strong> stream in the topology should explicitly add th=
e <em>SwimlaneTransformer </em>while defining the topology.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>add swimlane transformer</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">KStream=
&lt;String, SourceEvent&gt; events =3D builder.stream(sourceTopic);
events =3D events.transform(new SwimlaneTransformer&lt;&gt;());</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Check <a href=3D"https://bitbucket=
.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/wdp-inf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-=
meshrefstreamprocsr-v1-streamprocessor/browse/src/main/java/au/com/westpac/=
inf/bnkng/resrcitm/logclitcmpnt/meshrefstreamprocsr/v1/ReferenceStreamsTopo=
logyBuilder.java" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">reference stream=
 processor</a> for a sample implementation.</span></p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-9"><=
strong>9</strong></h2></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<h2 id=3D"StepstobuildaKafkaStreamProcessor-TestingStreamProcessorCodeLocal=
ly:"><strong>Testing Stream Processor Code Locally:</strong></h2>
<p>Just like a Kafka listener, stream processor can be run from on your loc=
al workstation with a little bit of configuration.</p>
</div><p>The process for testing your stream processor that connects to a t=
opic migrated to Confluent cloud is by using generic DEV credentials (early=
 adopter functional account) which has access to all topics in the DEV clus=
ter. Early adopter credentials for connecting to DEV Kafka cluster is provi=
ded in this page: <a href=3D"/display/MD/Early+Adopter+Credentials+for+Conf=
luent+Cloud+DEV+cluster">Early Adopter Credentials for Confluent Cloud DEV =
cluster</a></p><p>Follow the below steps to configure:</p>
<ul>
<li>Create a file named 'wdp-kafka.properties' in the env/local folder.</li=
>
<li>Update the file as shown in below sample titled wdp-kafka.properties.</=
li>
<li>Add the topic and group ID details to the file. This can be retrieved f=
rom the Configure access stage logs of the pipeline in stream processor dep=
loyment.</li>
<li>Create a file named 'wdp-kafka-secrets.properties' in secrets/local fol=
der.</li>
<li>Update the file as shown in below sample titled wdp-kafka-secrets.prope=
rties</li>
<li>At this moment, a stream processor cannot be run from mesh developer to=
ols. But the pom entries generated by the 'mesh init' include a cargo conta=
iner plugin which can be used to run the listener code.</li>
</ul><p><br></p>
<div id=3D"expander-565835968" class=3D"expand-container">
<div role=3D"heading" aria-level=3D"6" id=3D"expander-control-565835968" cl=
